  <num>1-621.06</num>
  <heading>Types of benefits.</heading>
  <para>
    <num>(a)</num>
    <text>The benefits provided under the health benefit plans shall include benefits for costs associated with care in a general hospital and for health services of a catastrophic nature and may include at a minimum the following benefits:</text>
    <para>
      <num>(1)</num>
      <text>Hospital benefits;</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>(2)</num>
      <text>Managed care;</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>(3)</num>
      <text>Office visits;</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>(4)</num>
      <text>Substance abuse;</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>(5)</num>
      <text>Well baby care;</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>(6)</num>
      <text>Prescription drugs;</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>(7)</num>
      <text>Obstetrical benefits;</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>(8)</num>
      <text>Mental health benefits; and</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>(9)</num>
      <text>Hospice care.</text>
    </para>
  </para>
  <para>
    <num>(b)</num>
    <text>Each contract issued under § <cite root="1-621.05">1-621.05</cite> shall comply with the provisions of Chapter 31 of Title 31.</text>
  </para>
